def: Holding lime or other earthy salts; as, the calcigerous cellsof the teeth.
To discharge with, or as with, a volley.
With a harsh, grating sound or voice.
Of or pertaining to the motions of fluids, or the forces whichproduce or affect such motions; -- opposed to hydrostatic. Sir W.Thomson.
A genus of polished marine gastropod shells, chiefly tropical,and often beautifully colored.
To cause to wheel or turn in an opposite direction.

Discovered or described by M. Tenon, a French anatomist.Tenonian capsule (Anat.), a lymphatic space inclosed by a delicatemembrane or fascia (the fascia of Tenon) between the eyeball and thefat of the orbit; -- called also capsule of Tenon.
Capable of being expiated or atoned for; as, an expiableoffense; expiable guilt. Bp. Hall.
An oval figure on monuments, and in papyri, containing the nameof a sovereign.
One who makes signals; one who communicates intelligence bymeans of signals.
